Lagos – People in positions of authority across the Nigeria have been tasked to provide effective leadership to in order to banish hunger, crime and insecurity from the country. Eze Michael E. Ezekwobi, Ezeudo, Ifako/Ijaiye Local Government Area, Lagos State, gave the charge in his new year message to the residents of the local government, adding that good leadership would reduce the challenges that the country is battling with. He called on Nigerians not to lose hope, adding that Nigeria will be great again. He argued that many great nations have passed through what Nigeria is passing through. Buhari Doesn’t Have Correct Information About Us –… 2023: South-East PDP Leaders Endorse Anyim’s Presidential… “Nigeria will come out of her problems virile, stronger and better,” the traditional ruler stated. He urged government at all levels to do something quickly on youth unemployment, which he described as a time bomb waiting to explode. Eze Ezekwobi thanked all those who supported his efforts to provide leadership and direction to people in Ifako/1jaiye Local Government Area. He expressed appreciation to “God Almighty for keeping all of us alive to see the year 2022.” He also called on Nigerians to be on their knees in prayers to God Almighty to “guide our leaders right and to grant them the right vision to lead Nigeria aright.” POLL He tasked Igbo people in Ifako/Tjaiye LGA to continue to maintain the peace and to continue to obey all constituted authorities all the time.